    </section>

    <p>The food thrown out in Sin­ga­pore last year weighed more than</p>
    <p>50,000 dou­ble decker buses. The food waste prob­lem here spans the sup­ply chain, from farm to fork. For a na­tion which loves food so much, why does such a huge chunk end up in the land­fill? In a new se­ries start­ing this week­end, The Sun­day Times takes you on a deep-dive into the coun­try ’s food sup­ply chain, to put food waste in the spot­light, and look at how farms, su­per­mar­kets, con­sumers and ground-up groups are sav­ing pro­duce from the bin.</p>

